129
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:12,700
No sleeping in. Get up.

130
00:07:12,700 --> 00:07:14,200
Where's Daddy?

131
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:17,000
Your dad is not home yet.

132
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,200
My stomach hurts. I don't want to go to school.

133
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:20,700
Liar. Get up.

134
00:07:20,700 --> 00:07:23,800
You can't be like this. Get up and have breakfast.

135
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:27,600
Shi Ke Yo is naughty.

136
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,200
Get up.

137
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:33,400
Don't do that.

138
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:35,100
Are you trying to tickle me?

139
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:37,600
You're a bad girl, Shi Ke Yo.

140
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:39,300
Stop it.

141
00:07:39,300 --> 00:07:42,900
Get up or else I'm going to carry you.

142
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:44,600
Yo Yo.

143
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,200
You don't want it?

144
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:50,900
How about... this?

145
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,900
Your daddy won't even know if you don't eat it.

146
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,500
You really wanted Daddy to eat breakfast with you, didn't you?

147
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:03,500
No.

148
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:05,500
I don't believe you.

149
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:07,500
That's why you don't want to eat when he's not here.

150
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:09,600
I said no.

151
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,300
Then, take a bite.

152
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:14,000
I'll believe you if you take a bite.

153
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:29,300
Is it good?

154
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,600
No.

155
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:32,900
No? But you seem to be enjoying it.

156
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:34,200
That's not true at all.

157
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:37,600
You want more? Didn't you say it wasn't good?

158
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,000
You stinky guys.

159
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:40,700
I hate all of you.

160
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:47,500
Yes, we are all stinky guys.

161
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:50,200
Our Yo Yo smells the best, right?

162
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,000
Then how about I eat breakfast with you?

163
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:52,700
Okay.

164
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:55,000
Great. Okay.

165
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,400
Do you want some juice?

166
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:57,100
No.

167
00:08:57,100 --> 00:08:58,700
What do you want to eat?

168
00:08:58,700 --> 00:09:00,500
You can't eat just that.

169
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:02,600
Have some kiwi.

170
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:07,000
Okay, drink some juice.

171
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:10,300
Don't force me to eat.

172
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:12,700
Okay, I won't force you.

173
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:18,200
Email me your wills before next Tuesday's class.

174
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:21,000
What?

175
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,300
"What" what?

176
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:25,700
Teacher, I already wrote a will in high school.

177
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:28,200
Then write it again.

178
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:30,600
If you copy what you wrote before,

179
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:34,100
it will show how childish and clueless you were back then.

180
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:35,300
I will have you guys learn

181
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:38,200
how hard it is to write a proper will.

182
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:41,000
Class dismissed.

183
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,700
He's indeed the Death Note.

184
00:09:42,700 --> 00:09:44,700
If the allotted time for class changes wasn't over,

185
00:09:44,700 --> 00:09:47,900
I would have switched out of this class long ago.

186
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:58,400
Teacher! I would like to speak with you.

187
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:09,200
Do you even remember that you have a daughter?

188
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,700
You haven't been home for five days.

189
00:10:10,700 --> 00:10:13,600
Are you that confident about just leaving her home alone?

190
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:16,400
You're there. Did you forget about that?

191
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:18,300
I hired you to be her nanny.

192
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:20,300
Do you even know me?

193
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:23,100
Am I a good or a bad person?

194
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:25,400
If I had wanted to do something to Yo Yo today,

195
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:27,700
would you have been able to protect her in time?

196
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:29,300
If you were a bad person

197
00:10:29,300 --> 00:10:32,000
you wouldn't be telling me all this right now.

198
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:35,200
Don't tell me

199
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:38,800
that you left her with a nanny the whole time before.

200
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:41,000
She would tell me if she didn't like it.

201
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,600
Who does she tell it to if you're not home?

202
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:45,700
You're her only family.

203
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:47,900
How could you treat her so heartlessly?

204
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:50,100
Letting a child be lonely and sad?

205
00:10:50,100 --> 00:10:52,100
What if she grows up with insecurities

206
00:10:52,100 --> 00:10:54,300
and goes down the wrong path?

207
00:10:54,300 --> 00:10:57,600
Whether someone becomes good or bad, it's personal to them.

208
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:01,500
F*ck. I can't believe you're actually a professor.

209
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:03,700
Fei Sheng Zhe, watch your tone.

210
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:05,300
You were a child once.

211
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:08,700
Do you not understand the feeling of wanting your parents' company?

212
00:11:08,700 --> 00:11:10,500
I don't.

213
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,500
Shi Yi Jie!

214
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:18,000
What a jerk.

215
00:11:19,900 --> 00:11:22,000
I only agreed because he couldn't find a nanny on such short notice.

216
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:24,300
Yo Yo is still too young to be left unattended.

217
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:26,400
Who knew that he wouldn't come home that day?

218
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:28,600
When he came home the next day, it was just to change his clothes.

219
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:30,800
Say, is there something wrong with his brain?

220
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:33,500
Is studying skeletons more important than his daughter?

221
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:34,600
Xiao Fei.

222
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:36,200
Does he even know

223
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:38,200
that raising a child is not like raising a pet?

224
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:40,800
It's not just giving them sunlight and wate--

225
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,800
Are you sure you want to continue complaining like an aunty?

226
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:47,800
I have no interest in hearing your domestic troubles.

227
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:49,500
Domestic troubles? Come on.

228
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:51,100
Yo Yo is only in Year One.

229
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:52,400
She's only seven.

230
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:55,200
This is when she needs her parent the most.

231
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,600
She doesn't have a mother.

232
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:59,300
The only person she can rely on is her heartless dad.

233
00:11:59,300 --> 00:12:02,200
And, then, he actually just leaves her in a stranger's care.

234
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:05,300
Come on. The kid is naive, not stupid. Okay?

235
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:07,000
She might not know what abandonment is,

236
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:10,700
but I'm sure she can tell if she's being loved or hated.

237
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:24,300
Bye-bye.

238
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:26,900
Yo Yo. Yo Yo.

239
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:29,700
Why are you here?

240
00:12:29,700 --> 00:12:31,700
I'm here to take you home.

241
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:34,200
Wait, we should buy some groceries first.

242
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:36,000
I don't want to.

243
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,700
Why not?

244
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:39,200
If you don't come with me,

245
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:40,400
I might buy the wrong thing.

246
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:42,000
What if I buy bell peppers?

247
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:42,900
Don't buy bell peppers.

248
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:44,900
I hate bell peppers.

249
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,700
All right, I won't buy bell peppers.

250
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:48,400
If you go with me, then I won't buy the wrong things.

251
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:49,900
All right? Come with me.

252
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:51,900
Okay.

253
00:12:59,100 --> 00:13:01,000
Where do I sit?

254
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,800
Oh, that's right.

255
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:09,400
Brother Xiao Fei, don't you think we look weird?

256
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,500
Where are we weird?

257
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:13,600
Because everyone else keeps staring at us.

258
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:15,900
Because they think we're so smart

259
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:19,200
since we thought to use the bike to carry the fruit.

260
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:21,600
No, they're laughing.

261
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:22,700
They're laughing

262
00:13:22,700 --> 00:13:24,300
because Yo Yo is cute.

263
00:13:24,300 --> 00:13:25,800
No, they're not.

264
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:27,800
They don't think I'm cute.

265
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:29,100
How do you know what they're thinking?

266
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:31,800
They feel happy when they see you, so they laugh.

267
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:33,600
Isn't that right?

268
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:36,700
What do you want to eat tonight?

269
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:39,300
Omelette rice!

270
00:13:39,300 --> 00:13:41,100
Let's hurry home so I can make it for you. Okay?

271
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:41,500
Okay.

272
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:42,300
Let's speed up then. Okay?

