00:13:42,300 --> 00:13:43,400
Okay.

274
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:44,700
Speed up.

275
00:13:44,700 --> 00:13:46,300
Stop.

276
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:47,500
Why are we stopping?

277
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:49,100
Let's see...

278
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,900
who will reach home first!

279
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:51,400
Start!

280
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:54,200
That's not fair. I'm going to ride the bike.

281
00:13:57,300 --> 00:13:58,800
Run faster, Yo Yo.

282
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:00,900
I'm catching up to you.

283
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:14,400
Are you done?

284
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:16,700
Yo Yo, I'm almost done.

285
00:14:16,700 --> 00:14:19,090
Just wait a bit more, okay?

286
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:33,100
Do you even know how to do it?

287
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:34,600
You're supposed to wait for me.

288
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,700
Be good, okay?

289
00:14:36,700 --> 00:14:38,700
Another two minutes.

290
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:53,700
Are you done? I'm so hungry.

291
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:56,900
Take this first then.

292
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:01,700
Don't nibble it.

293
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:11,700
Here.

294
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:15,700
The delicious omelette rice

295
00:15:15,700 --> 00:15:18,700
with Xiao Fei's special salad.

296
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,200
Let's eat.

297
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:29,100
What's wrong?

298
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:31,700
Why isn't there a smiley face on top?

299
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:35,000
Before, my mom used to draw a smiley face on it.

300
00:15:35,900 --> 00:15:38,100
Why does a smiley face have such a dark history?

301
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:40,700
I'll draw one for you.

302
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:43,100
What's a dark history?

303
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:46,700
A dark history is...

304
00:15:46,700 --> 00:15:48,400
You'll understand it when you're older.

305
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:50,000
Here.

306
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:52,400
A smiley face, right?

307
00:15:52,400 --> 00:15:54,100
Yes.

308
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:57,000
Oh, it's angry.

309
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,900
Nose...

310
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:00,700
It's not like that.

311
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:03,900
Why not? It looks nice.

312
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:06,100
You should draw the mouth like this.

313
00:16:06,100 --> 00:16:07,300
See? Like this.

314
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:09,500
And this is the nose.

315
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:12,000
You forgot the nose.

316
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:13,400
The nose is too big.

317
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:15,700
It's okay. I like it.

318
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:17,300
Why don't you draw it for me, too?

319
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:20,000
Okay, I'll fill in your mouth.

320
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:21,100
Yours is bigger,

321
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:23,700
so I'm drawing a bigger one.

322
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:27,200
Okay.

323
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:30,300
Okay. I'll practice how to draw smiley faces later.

324
00:16:30,300 --> 00:16:31,300
Okay.

325
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:31,800
Let's eat.

326
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:33,800
Let's eat.

327
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:04,600
Mom,

328
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:07,400
you're on the extra night shift today. Right?

329
00:17:09,900 --> 00:17:11,600
Okay.

330
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:15,700
Please find the time to get some rest.

331
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:16,800
Okay.

332
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:18,400
I know.

333
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:20,000
Bye-bye.

334
00:17:24,300 --> 00:17:25,500
Yo Yo,

335
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:27,300
are you sure your daddy will eat this?

336
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:31,400
Yes. He always eats the food I leave for him.

337
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:37,400
That's not how you use, "holding the fort."

338
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:39,900
Stop using idioms if you're going to use them wrong, Mister.

339
00:17:39,900 --> 00:17:42,500
That's not the point.

340
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:44,900
The point is,

341
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:47,200
do you have any idea how to solve this problem?

342
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:49,900
Compared to that, you should worry about your will first.

343
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:51,800
Have you written it?

344
00:17:51,800 --> 00:17:52,900
I don't want to.

345
00:17:52,900 --> 00:17:54,700
Don't be so stubborn.

346
00:17:54,700 --> 00:17:56,800
Listen, I asked Zhou Shao An

347
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:59,600
and he said Shi Yi Jie really strikes people off and fails them.

348
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:01,400
Don't take your credit points lightly.

349
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,800
Okay, okay, I know.

350
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:06,200
Brother Xiao Fei, I'm done showering,

351
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:07,700
but I forgot my towel.

352
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:09,000
Can you bring it to me?

353
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:12,600
Okay, Yo Yo. Hold on. I'll be right there.

354
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:13,900
Hey, I can't talk to you any longer.

355
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:15,900
Yo Yo is done showering. I'm going to ger her a towel.

356
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:16,500
Bye-bye.

357
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:18,500
Hey, wait.

358
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:24,500
That guy is addicted to being a nanny.

359
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:50,900
Daddy, my stomach hurts.

360
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:52,600
Yo Yo.

361
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:57,200
What's wrong, Yo Yo?

362
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:58,300
Where are you hurting, Yo Yo?

363
00:18:58,300 --> 00:18:59,400
My stomach.

364
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,500
Your stomach hurts?

365
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,600
Here?

366
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:04,100
Don't shout. Don't shout.

367
00:19:04,100 --> 00:19:05,900
Hang in there. I'll take you to the hospital. Okay?

368
00:19:05,900 --> 00:19:06,600
Okay.

369
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:08,500
It's all right. It's all right.

370
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:09,500
I'll take you to the hospital.

371
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:09,900
It hurts.

372
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:11,200
It's okay.

373
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:12,900
Really?

374
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:14,800
That's great!

375
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:18,400
I didn't think there would be more relics after the White Bone Pit.

376
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:21,300
This is a huge discovery. I'm very interested.

377
00:19:29,100 --> 00:19:30,400
Why don't we do this?

378
00:19:30,400 --> 00:19:32,000
Send me your files first.

379
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,800
I'll take a look and get back to you.

380
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:36,200
All right.

381
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:37,300
Okay.

382
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:39,600
Okay. Then let's leave it like this. Thank you.

383
00:19:47,350 --> 00:19:51,290
[Emergency Room]

384
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:53,500
Fei Sheng Zhe.

385
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:55,300
Where's Yo Yo?

386
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:57,900
I called you so many times.

387
00:19:57,900 --> 00:20:00,600
Do you know what happened to Yo Yo?

388
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:02,100
Neurogenic gastritis.

389
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:03,800
What kind of stress is she under to suffer from that?

390
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:05,000
Where is Yo Yo?

391
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:07,800
Do you know what Yo Yo needs?

392
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:10,600
She needs a real father.

393
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:13,300
One who stays by her side and helps her with homework...

394
00:20:13,300 --> 00:20:15,300
and walks her to school.

395
00:20:15,300 --> 00:20:17,300
Not some skeleton researcher...

396
00:20:17,300 --> 00:20:19,400
who leaves her with a nanny.

397
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:22,100
You don't deserve to be a father.

398
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:25,500
You're nothing but a jerk!

399
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:27,800
That's enough. That's enough.

400
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:30,000
Be quiet, this is a hospital.

401
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,600
Mom.

402
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:40,600
You're Ah Jie, right?

403
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,600
Sister Juan?

404
00:21:04,150 --> 00:21:05,150
Why are you still like before,

405
00:21:05,150 --> 00:21:07,850
always having a sour face?

406
00:21:07,850 --> 00:21:09,350
Give me a smile.

407
00:21:09,350 --> 00:21:11,350
Don't always have on a sour face.

408
00:21:11,350 --> 00:21:13,450
You'll scare the children.

409
00:21:13,450 --> 00:21:15,050
Sister Juan.

410
00:21:16,050 --> 00:21:18,250
All right. After this,

411
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:20,150
get her medicine. After her drip infusion is done,

412
00:21:20,150 --> 00:21:23,250
you'll be able to take your daughter home.

413
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:24,750
Thank you, Sister Juan.

414
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:26,750
You're welcome.

415
00:21:28,150 --> 00:21:30,050
I didn't think that Fei Sheng Zhe would be your son.

416
00:21:30,050 --> 00:21:34,350
And I didn't think the heartless father he talks about is you.

417
00:21:36,450 --> 00:21:38,850
Indeed, I'm not fit to be a father.

418
00:21:41,550 --> 00:21:43,650
Actually, everyone

419
00:21:43,650 --> 00:21:49,050
learns how to become parents only after they have kids.

420
00:21:49,050 --> 00:21:51,250
There's no need to be depressed.

421
00:21:53,450 --> 00:21:55,850
I'm sorry.

422
00:21:55,850 --> 00:21:58,650
My son is quite sensitive about this matter.

423
00:21:58,650 --> 00:21:59,850
That's probably because

424
00:21:59,850 --> 00:22:02,650
he only has a mother who's always busy with work.

425
00:22:02,650 --> 00:22:06,450
Since young, I haven't had time to take good care of him.

426
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:07,850
So, he has always been lonely.

427
00:22:07,850 --> 00:22:11,350
Even worse, because of my negligence,

428
00:22:11,350 --> 00:22:14,150
he once got hurt.

429
00:22:20,250 --> 00:22:22,550
I guess it's for this reason,

430
00:22:22,550 --> 00:22:25,750
he decided to agree to take this job.

431
00:22:25,750 --> 00:22:27,650
Because your daughter is in

432
00:22:27,650 --> 00:22:30,550
a similar situation to his own at one time.

433
00:22:57,050 --> 00:23:00,550
How does she tell you if you're not home?

434
00:23:00,550 --> 00:23:02,850
You're her only family.

435
00:23:02,850 --> 00:23:04,650
How could you treat her so heartlessly?

436
00:23:04,650 --> 00:23:06,350
You were a child once.

437
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:10,250
Do you not understand the feeling of wanting your parents' company?

438
00:23:16,950 --> 00:23:19,550
Daddy, where's Brother Xiao Fei?

439
00:23:19,550 --> 00:23:21,250
He has gone home.

440
00:23:21,250 --> 00:23:22,350
Does your stomach still hurt?

441
00:23:22,350 --> 00:23:24,850
A little bit.

442
00:23:24,850 --> 00:23:26,850
Let me tell you.

443
00:23:26,850 --> 00:23:30,050
He carried me to the car

444
00:23:30,050 --> 00:23:33,150
and also took me to the hospital.

445
00:23:33,150 --> 00:23:34,950
He even cried.

446
00:23:34,950 --> 00:23:38,550
But I didn't cry. I even comforted him.

447
00:23:38,550 --> 00:23:40,750
He couldn't find you,

448
00:23:40,750 --> 00:23:42,550
so he cried.

449
00:23:42,550 --> 00:23:45,150
But luckily you came.

450
00:23:45,150 --> 00:23:47,950
And I stopped hurting.

451
00:24:12,250 --> 00:24:16,950
Mom, how do you know Shi Yi Jie?

452
00:24:16,950 --> 00:24:19,950
It was probably about ten years ago.

453
00:24:19,950 --> 00:24:23,150
I was volunteering at an orphanage.

454
00:24:23,150 --> 00:24:25,450
It so happened that he came back for a visit.

455
00:24:25,450 --> 00:24:27,350
Came back?

456
00:24:27,350 --> 00:24:29,050
You mean,

457
00:24:29,050 --> 00:24:32,150
he grew up in an orphanage?

458
00:24:32,150 --> 00:24:35,250
I also heard it from the Dean.

459
00:24:35,250 --> 00:24:38,250
His family of four went on a trip one time;

460
00:24:38,250 --> 00:24:40,050
and at its end, an accident happened.

461
00:24:40,050 --> 00:24:42,350
He was the only one who survived.

462
00:24:42,350 --> 00:24:45,450
But, like a rubber ball,

463
00:24:45,450 --> 00:24:46,650
he kept being tossed around, here and there,

464
00:24:46,650 --> 00:24:49,750
by his relatives.

465
00:24:49,750 --> 00:24:51,450
Ultimately,

466
00:24:51,450 --> 00:24:53,650
he had to go to an orphanage.

467
00:24:54,950 --> 00:24:57,350
I didn't think that guy's dark history

468
00:24:57,350 --> 00:24:59,850
would really be this dark.

469
00:25:03,450 --> 00:25:07,150
Will Brother Xiao Fei come tomorrow?

470
00:25:07,150 --> 00:25:08,350
Do you like him?

471
00:25:08,350 --> 00:25:09,050
Yes.

472
00:25:09,050 --> 00:25:11,850
I like to eat his omelette rice.

473
00:25:11,850 --> 00:25:14,250
He helps me with my homework after we eat.

474
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:17,550
He also signs my contact book after I finish my homework.

475
00:25:17,550 --> 00:25:20,750
He comes to school to pick me up on his bicycle.

476
00:25:20,750 --> 00:25:23,250
He brings me along when he buys groceries.

477
00:25:24,850 --> 00:25:26,450
Go to sleep if you want to.

478
00:25:26,450 --> 00:25:30,550
No. I want to talk with you.

479
00:25:30,550 --> 00:25:32,050
Let me tell you.

480
00:25:32,050 --> 00:25:35,150
I got 100% on my test this week.

481
00:25:35,150 --> 00:25:37,850
I bought gummies for you.

482
00:25:37,850 --> 00:25:39,550
But since you didn't come home,

483
00:25:39,550 --> 00:25:42,150
I ate it myself.

484
00:25:43,350 --> 00:25:45,450
Daddy is sorry.

485
00:25:45,450 --> 00:25:47,150
Next time, tell me if you bought me gummies.

486
00:25:47,150 --> 00:25:49,550
I'll make sure to come back and eat them.

487
00:26:31,350 --> 00:26:34,150
They're probably asleep by now.

488
00:26:40,250 --> 00:26:41,850
I beat him up and criticized him at the hospital today.

489
00:26:41,850 --> 00:26:44,350
Why would he want to see me?

490
00:26:45,950 --> 00:26:48,950
What if he really fails me?

491
00:26:50,150 --> 00:26:52,850
Why did I have to be so rash?

492
00:26:56,050 --> 00:26:59,150
It's too late for regrets now.

493
00:27:12,950 --> 00:27:14,950
Delivery?

494
00:27:19,750 --> 00:27:21,450
You bought pudding?

495
00:27:21,450 --> 00:27:23,650
Yo Yo likes it.

496
00:27:23,650 --> 00:27:25,450
Bread?

497
00:27:26,250 --> 00:27:29,250
I reckon you guys are too busy to make breakfast.

498
00:27:30,750 --> 00:27:32,950
Do I drink milk?

499
00:27:32,950 --> 00:27:35,450
Children need it to grow.

500
00:27:40,050 --> 00:27:41,850
Apples?

501
00:27:43,150 --> 00:27:45,450
It's good for the skin.

502
00:27:45,450 --> 00:27:47,250
I want to eat omelette rice.

503
00:27:47,250 --> 00:27:48,850
What?

504
00:28:19,150 --> 00:28:20,350
What are you looking at?

505
00:28:20,350 --> 00:28:22,250
Have you never seen someone beating eggs?

506
00:28:23,150 --> 00:28:25,150
I have never seen someone beating eggs for that long.

507
00:28:25,850 --> 00:28:27,450
If you beat it longer, more air gets into it

508
00:28:27,450 --> 00:28:28,150
and the eggs will become fluffier.

509
00:28:28,150 --> 00:28:29,650
What would you know?

510
00:28:29,650 --> 00:28:32,350
Why would you need fluffy eggs for omelette rice?

511
00:28:33,550 --> 00:28:35,350
Mine do.

512
00:28:49,450 --> 00:28:52,950
Enjoy the food. I'm leaving now.

513
00:28:52,950 --> 00:28:54,950
Let's eat together.

514
00:28:56,550 --> 00:28:58,350
This fluffy omelette is suspicious.

515
00:28:58,350 --> 00:29:00,050
If anything were to happen,

516
00:29:00,050 --> 00:29:02,550
at least it will happen to both of us.

517
00:29:13,950 --> 00:29:15,550
Eat up.

518
00:29:43,750 --> 00:29:45,650
Hey, I want a beer, too.

519
00:29:45,650 --> 00:29:47,150
You're not of age yet.

520
00:29:47,150 --> 00:29:48,550
I'm already 19.

521
00:29:48,550 --> 00:29:50,750
I can buy my own alcohol.

522
00:29:50,750 --> 00:29:52,350
Really?

523
00:29:52,350 --> 00:29:55,050
That's too bad. This is the last can in the fridge.

524
00:30:00,550 --> 00:30:03,650
I don't believe that you had your first beer only after you came of age.

525
00:30:03,650 --> 00:30:05,310
I did.

526
00:30:06,050 --> 00:30:07,750
Really?

527
00:30:07,750 --> 00:30:08,650
I wouldn't ask someone

528
00:30:08,650 --> 00:30:11,350
to do the things that I couldn't.

529
00:30:11,350 --> 00:30:14,750
Drink your juice, brat.

530
00:30:30,150 --> 00:30:32,250
When you were young--

531
00:30:34,650 --> 00:30:36,750
Why did you stop asking?

532
00:30:39,350 --> 00:30:41,550
Well?

533
00:30:41,550 --> 00:30:43,750
Are you afraid of bringing up sad memories

534
00:30:43,750 --> 00:30:46,250
and making the other person feel bad,

535
00:30:46,250 --> 00:30:48,450
so you avoid the matter?

536
00:30:49,850 --> 00:30:51,650
Do you know that your pretense

537
00:30:51,650 --> 00:30:54,550
is more hurtful to others?

538
00:30:54,550 --> 00:30:57,550
You might as well be straightforward and just ask.

539
00:30:58,150 --> 00:31:01,990
So, I can ask about it?

540
00:31:02,950 --> 00:31:04,950
But I don't wish to answer it.

541
00:31:05,650 --> 00:31:07,850
Are you kidding me?

542
00:31:18,050 --> 00:31:19,650
Cheers.

543
00:31:20,550 --> 00:31:23,350
Thank you for taking care of Yo Yo today.

544
00:31:23,350 --> 00:31:25,450
You must have been scared.

545
00:31:28,950 --> 00:31:31,550
It was my first time encountering that situation.

546
00:31:31,550 --> 00:31:33,450
Yo Yo is still so young

547
00:31:33,450 --> 00:31:35,350
and she was in so much pain.

548
00:31:35,350 --> 00:31:38,480
I thought the food I cooked made her sick.

549
00:31:47,650 --> 00:31:49,950
You did well.

550
00:31:49,950 --> 00:31:51,750
Thank you.

551
00:31:53,650 --> 00:31:54,950
What are you doing?

552
00:31:54,950 --> 00:31:56,650
